===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[derogatory]] term for an [[Englishman]].  

====Usage note====
Insular Celts who still refer to the English as "[[Saxon]]", are citing their cultural roots as 5th century barbarian invaders who overwhelmed the Celts.  The implication is that after fifteen hunderd years of occupying southern Britain, the English are still unwanted outsiders, not true natives of the island.

